[SN]TITLE[SN]
Orkney public toilet put up for sale

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
The sale of a former public toilet in Orkney has flushed out interest from around the world, according to the local council.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The toilet at Mayburn Court in Stromness is just 28ft by 9ft in size.
It is being sold for offers over Â£5,000.
Orkney Islands Council said it has generated interest from around the world. The toilet is close to the former home of the late poet George MacKay Brown.
